The paper focuses on fairness issues in two-sided market platforms, specifically in the context of recommendation systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of an ILP-based online optimization algorithm, which suggests that it may also belong to the Optimization and Control (cs.CY) category. The paper also discusses the social implications of platform updates, which suggests that it may belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or the Computers and Society (cs.SOC) categories.
